What not to do when you are comforting someone:
Reassure or Distract. The first set is the least worst things you can say. ...
Condemn or Criticize Their Behavior. ...
Tell Them How to Behave. ...
Delegitimize Their Feelings. ...
Make Them Feel Inferior. ...
Tell Them How to Feel. ...
Focus on Your Own Feelings. ...
Over-Involve Yourself in Their Life.
From "WHAT NOT TO SAY TO COMFORT A FRIEND (PSYCHOLOGY OF RELATIONSHIPS)"
